<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n25078i"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n25" href="#n25078i">N25 (VI.B.15)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n25all.htm#n25078i"> 78(i)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> little pig / Sowy (a boy) / Boartha (a girl)</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">The world-wide belief in the invisible powers as, in the main, keen to pounce on mortals, explains the Chinese custom of <mark>giving their boys a girl&apos;s name</mark> to deceive the gods; sometimes tabooing names altogether, and calling the child <mark>&lsquo;little pig&rsquo; or &lsquo;little dog.&rsquo;</mark> <small> Edward Clodd, <a name="ECTTT" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#ECTTT"><cite title="source">Tom Tit Tot</cite></a> (1898) 131</small></blockquote> <mm class="note">Raphael transcription: <a name="c14047d" href="c14all.htm#c14047d">VI.C.14:047(d)</a>, <a name="c14047e" href="c14all.htm#c14047e">VI.C.14:047(e)</a>, <a name="c14047f" href="c14all.htm#c14047f">VI.C.14:047(f)</a> </mm></dd> </dd></dl>
